\subsection{\href{https://beta.lmfdb.org/knowledge/show/hgm.zigzagplot}{Zigzag plot}}
\begin{definition}\label{hgm.zigzagplot}
\uses{hgm.defining_parameters,hgm.hodge_vector}
The \textbf{zigzag plot}, or \textbf{zigzag procedure}, is a graphical representation of the \hyperref[hgm.defining_parameters]{defining parameters of a hypergeometric family} $\alpha$ and $\beta$. For improved readability, we color the $\alpha$ parameters with red, and the $\beta$ parameters with blue. It is constructed by ordering the parameters $\alpha_i$ and $\beta_j$. One draws a point at $(0,0)$ corresponding to the lowest parameter. One then proceeds in uniform steps from left to right, drawing a point for each parameter and then moving diagonally upwards after red points and diagonally downwards after blue points. 

The \hyperref[hgm.hodge_vector]{hodge vector} of the corresponding hypergeometric family can be read from the Zigzag plot by counting the number of points of the same color lying on each horizontal line.
\end{definition}


